'''Baird Brothers Fine Hardwoods''' is a privately held manufacturer and retailer of interior [[Hardwood|hardwood products]]. It has been family owned and operated since 1960. The company is headquartered in [[Canfield, Ohio]].

Baird Brothers manufactures and retails interior hardwood products. The company produces products as simple as dimensional lumber and hardwood flooring, to custom doors, mouldings, and other products.<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":5" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Technology Updates the Craftsman's Eye at Baird |url=http://archive.businessjournaldaily.com/company-news/technology-updates-craftsmans-eye-baird-2014-9-3 |website=Business Journal Daily |language=en}}</ref>

== History ==
Baird Brothers Fine Hardwoods, also known by its incorporated name, Baird Brothers Sawmill, was founded in 1960.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.vindy.com/news/2015/may/24/rooted-in-valley/|title=Baird Brothers busy building|website=The Vindicator|access-date=2018-01-22}}</ref>

President Paul Baird, the last surviving founder, but the company still remains a family owned and operated business. Now into their second generation, the family business is conducted by Scott Baird, Mark Baird, Matt Baird, Lori Baird, Terry Baird, and Tim Baird.<ref name=":5">{{Cite news|url=https://businessjournaldaily.com/baird-brothers-festival-will-showcase-its-craftsmanship/|title=Baird Brothers Festival Will Showcase Its Craftsmanship - Business Journal Daily|date=2017-09-18|work=Business Journal Daily|access-date=2018-01-22|language=en-US}}</ref>

Currently the company operates all of its business through its headquarters in [[Canfield, Ohio]], doing most of its business through online and phone sales.<ref name=":2" /> Baird Brothers has an annual festival named the "Red White & True Fall Festival".<ref>{{cite web|title=Baird Brothers celebrates American craftsmanship at fall festival|url=http://www.vindy.com/news/2012/oct/19/baird-brothers-celebrates-american-craft/?print|website=The Vindicator}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vindy.com/news/2014/sep/28/by-sean-barron/|title=Baird Bros. event offers carpentry projects, demos, tours|website=The Vindicator|access-date=2018-01-22}}</ref> The company has evolved from a small operation to a nationwide corporation housing their finished product in warehouses spanning more than 200 yards.<ref name=":5" />

